<br>
So I snared the high elf chick and starting to single kite her, letting the 2 gnomes duke it out, had the high elf chick around 40% or so when I went back to the gnomes to get the killing blow on the one gnome. Indeed it was 3% aaxp. Very nice. So I rooted him since he was at like 90% (stupid complete heal) and continued to kite the high elf chick. Ran OOM. No KEI. Ran past a brushhopper and it aggroed on the high elf chick, YAY! Free damage, don't even need more mana. Ran past a wolf and he aggroed too. Waited till she got to like 5% hp and rooted her so she killed the adds. Then one ice spear = dead. 6% aaxp for something like 10 mins of work.<br>
<br>
Tough quad, impossible I think. The caster is too much, plus they have a ton of hp. I'd probably have to guess like 15k. I think my single ice spear on the high elf chick took her to 94% with 1200 damage (no mage bracer). So if you work out the math it says she has 18800 hp. I don't know I might have misjudged. Anyway they are TOUGH. Dual quadding is possible if you can find a way to deal with the cleric. Fun to do though, got a roxor phat leather whip off the high elf chick.<br>
<br>
Its possible if you can always get the 2 gnomes to aggro and find a consistant source of wolves/rockhoppers to get some decent exp but I doubt it.<br>
<br>
Fun to try at least... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugarielhalliwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gariel Halliwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/13/02 7:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3% exp from single kite.. WHERE?</span><hr size=1> What is the /loc of these mobs and do they have a faction hit?<br>
